# gdm is the session launcher: it is wired up (gdm user/group, PAM,
# custom.conf with WaylandEnable + automatic login of `user`, and a
# wayland-sessions/gnome.desktop), so let the vendor default enable it. Presets
# are reapplied on every boot here (volatile /etc, empty machine-id). The old
# tty1-autologin -> user gnome-shell.service path is retired (its autologin.conf
# and graphical-session.sh are removed) so it does not fight gdm for seat0.

# Diagnostic root console on the second serial port (ttyS1). The qemu runner
# wires ttyS1 to a host unix socket (diag.sock) so the agent can drive the guest
# over it. A concrete unit (not a serial-getty@ instance) is used because
# preset-all does not instantiate template units by instance name; a concrete
# unit with [Install] is enabled here reliably. ttyS0 stays the user console.
enable diag-console.service
